    <h2 id="tips">Tips for Getting the Best Results from Constipation Gummies</h2>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Start slowly and increase gradually</strong>
        <p>Begin with half the recommended serving for the first 5-7 days, then increase to the full dose. This gradual approach allows your gut bacteria to adapt and significantly reduces gas and bloating during the adjustment period.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Drink adequate water — at least 8oz per serving</strong>
        <p>Fiber needs water to form the gel that softens stool. Without enough water, fiber can actually worsen constipation by creating hard, dry bulk in the colon. Aim for at least 8 ounces of water with each fiber gummy serving.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Be consistent — daily use produces best results</strong>
        <p>Fiber supplementation works best with daily consistency over weeks and months. Occasional use provides limited benefit. Set a daily reminder and take your gummies at the same time each day to establish a routine.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Combine with dietary fiber sources</strong>
        <p>Gummies supplement your dietary fiber — they do not replace it. Continue eating fiber-rich foods like fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and legumes. The combination of dietary and supplemental fiber produces the best regularity outcomes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

